In [[telecommunication]], the term '''remote access''' has the following meanings: 

#Pertaining to communication with a [[data processing]] [[facility]] from a remote location or facility through a [[data link]]. 
#A [[PABX]] [[service feature]] that allows a [[User (telecommunications)|user]] at a remote location to [[access]] by [[telephone]] PABX features, such as access to [[Wide Area Telephone Service]] (WATS) lines. 

''Note:''  For remote access, individual [[authorization]] codes are usually required.

'''Source:''' From [[Federal Standard 1037C]]

'''Remote Access''' is also the name of a successful [[DOS]]-based [[Bulletin board system|BBS]] software.

